.
 Recently, the TFA has also been used to study olfaction, either in the
 fixed tethered configuration 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Bhandawat:2010eu"

\end_inset

 or in rotatable tethered configiration, where flies can actively reoirent
 into or away from an odorised airstream 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Frye:2003da,Frye:2004gj,Krishnan:2011eb"

\end_inset

.
 Since the fly is fixed in place in this assay, it allows delivering and
 measuring olfactroy stimuli and measuring how these olfactroy stimuli modualte
 olfactroy flight behavior.
 In this assay, the behavior of the fly is quantified by changes in the
 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
